</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I would like to think that eventually it could be worked in that a Cleric's direct-damage-to-undead spells would have bonuses against PvP Necromancers and Shadow Knights.....but you never know.

<P>That's opening a whole new can of worms, and would turn PvP into a veritable game of Paper, Rocks, Scissors.
<P>Clerics beat Necros, but are beaten by Wizards who are beaten by Monks who are beaten by.....etc.
<P>As far as Clerics <i>currently</i> being viable at solo PvP....I don't know. If extrapolated to a PvE <i>group</i> encounter, I know for a fact that they can be very valuable. I can only surmise that they will come well into play in group PvP battles.
<P>Do us a favor. Test it out and report it. It's what we are there for :)
<P>Zariin
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
